 <title>The Rise and Fall of New Media</title>
 <link>http://varnelis.net/blog/the_rise_and_fall_of_new_media</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;My essay &amp;quot;the Rise and Fall of New Media&amp;quot; can be found in the twentieth anniversary issue of Frieze and online their site &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.frieze.com/issue/article/down-the-line/&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. It&amp;#39;s paired with an essay by Lauren Cornell of Rhizome and the New Museum. Together, both deal with the issue that far from being a niche interest, as Cornell writes, &amp;quot;every kind of artistic practice has been touched by the Internet as both a tool and as something that affects us in a broader sense&amp;hellip;&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Posting has been light this summer as I&amp;#39;ve moved into a new house (modernism, even!) but things have been moving behind the scenes. With the new semester coming up, expect more on the way.&lt;/p&gt;
